<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-09-16T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-09-16T14:00:00-05:00" n="597" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d597">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.515/745a: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-09-16T15:00:00-04:00">September 16, 1935—3
                                    p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>286. Department desires that in any contacts which you may have with
                            Leith-Ross you adopt friendly attitude and if approached by him on
                            official subjects be cooperative.</p>
                        <p>If he inquires whether this Government intends to send a financial
                            attaché, reply as on your own responsibility that you “infer that it
                            will not do so.”</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>